tools.name: Subscribe to channel
tools.description: Subscribes the authenticated user to a specified YouTube channel, identified by its unique `channelId` which must be valid and existing.

channelId.description: Unique identifier (ID) of the YouTube channel to subscribe to (typically starts with 'UC').
channelId.title: Channel Id

response_data.description: YouTube Subscription resource returned after subscribing to a channel.
response_data.title: Response Data

contentDetails.description: Additional details and basic stats about the subscription. Included if 'contentDetails' is specified in the 'part' parameter.
contentDetails.title: SubscriptionContentDetails

activityType.description: Specifies the activity type associated with the subscription. Common values include 'all' (all activities) and 'uploads' (new uploads).
activityType.title: Activity Type

newItemCount.description: Number of new items (e.g., new uploads) since the last time the user checked the subscription.
newItemCount.title: New Item Count

totalItemCount.description: Total number of items associated with the subscription (e.g., total uploaded videos for the subscribed channel).
totalItemCount.title: Total Item Count

etag.description: ETag of the resource, used for caching and concurrency control.
etag.title: Etag

kind.description: Identifies the resource type. For a subscription resource, the value is 'youtube#subscription'.
kind.title: Kind

snippet.description: Basic details about the subscription and the channel being subscribed to. Included if 'snippet' is specified in the 'part' parameter.
snippet.title: SubscriptionSnippet

channelId.description: The channel ID of the authenticated user (subscriber) that owns this subscription.
channelId.title: Channel Id

description.description: A short description associated with the subscribed channel.
description.title: Description

publishedAt.description: The date and time the subscription was created, in ISO 8601/RFC3339 format.
publishedAt.title: Published At

resourceId.description: Identifies the target resource that the user subscribed to.
resourceId.title: Resource Id

channelId.description: The channel ID of the channel that the user subscribed to.
channelId.title: Channel Id

kind.description: Type of the subscribed resource. For channel subscriptions, this is typically 'youtube#channel'.
kind.title: Kind

thumbnails.description: A set of thumbnails for the subscribed channel. Each property is optional and may be absent depending on availability.
thumbnails.title: Thumbnails

title.description: Title of the channel to which the user subscribed.
title.title: Title

subscriberSnippet.description: Details about the subscriber (the channel that created the subscription). Included if 'subscriberSnippet' is specified in the 'part' parameter and applicable to the request.
subscriberSnippet.title: SubscriberSnippet

channelId.description: Channel ID of the subscriber’s channel.
channelId.title: Channel Id

thumbnails.description: A set of thumbnails for the subscriber’s channel. Each property is optional and may be absent depending on availability.
thumbnails.title: Thumbnails

error.description: Error if any occurred during the execution of the action
error.title: Error

successful.description: Whether or not the action execution was successful or not
successful.title: Successful

tools.name: Update thumbnail
tools.description: Sets the custom thumbnail for a YouTube video using an image from thumbnailUrl; the authenticated user must have permission to edit the video.

thumbnailUrl.description: Publicly accessible URL of the new thumbnail image. Must be JPG, GIF, or PNG; under 2MB. Recommended: 16:9 aspect ratio, 1280x720 resolution (minimum 640px width).
thumbnailUrl.title: Thumbnail Url

videoId.description: Identifier of the YouTube video for which to update the thumbnail.
videoId.title: Video Id

etag.description: The ETag of this resource, used for caching and concurrency control.

items.description: A list of thumbnail detail objects for the video. Typically contains a single entry; enumerates the available thumbnail sizes after the update.
items.title: Items

default.description: The default thumbnail for the video (commonly 120x90). Present only if available.
default.title: YouTubeThumbnail

height.description: The height of the thumbnail image in pixels. May be omitted.
height.title: Height

url.description: A fully qualified URL pointing to the thumbnail image.
url.title: Url

width.description: The width of the thumbnail image in pixels. May be omitted.
width.title: Width

high.description: The high-resolution thumbnail for the video (commonly 480x360). Present only if available.

url.description: A fully qualified URL pointing to the thumbnail image.

width.description: The width of the thumbnail image in pixels. May be omitted.
width.title: Width

maxres.description: The maximum-resolution thumbnail for the video (commonly 1280x720). Present only if available; not all videos have a max resolution thumbnail.
maxres.title: YouTubeThumbnail

height.description: The height of the thumbnail image in pixels. May be omitted.
height.title: Height

url.description: A fully qualified URL pointing to the thumbnail image.
url.title: Url

width.description: The width of the thumbnail image in pixels. May be omitted.
width.title: Width

medium.description: The medium thumbnail for the video (commonly 320x180). Present only if available.
medium.title: YouTubeThumbnail

height.title: Height

url.description: A fully qualified URL pointing to the thumbnail image.
url.title: Url

width.description: The width of the thumbnail image in pixels. May be omitted.
width.title: Width

standard.description: The standard-resolution thumbnail for the video (commonly 640x480). Present only if available; many videos may not include this size.
standard.title: YouTubeThumbnail

tools.name: Update video
tools.description: Updates metadata for a YouTube video identified by videoId, which must exist; an empty list for tags removes all existing tags.

categoryId.description: New YouTube category ID. No change if omitted or `None`.
categoryId.title: Category Id

description.description: New video description. No change if omitted or `None`.
description.title: Description
examples: This is an updated description of my awesome video.

privacyStatus.description: New privacy status ('public', 'private', or 'unlisted'). No change if omitted or `None`.
privacyStatus.title: Privacy Status

tags.description: New tags, replacing all existing. An empty list removes all. No change if omitted or `None`.
tags.title: Tags

title.description: New video title. No change if omitted or `None`.
title.title: Title

videoId.description: The video's unique YouTube ID, typically found in its URL.
videoId.title: Video Id

error.description: Error if any occurred during the execution of the action
error.title: Error

successful.description: Whether or not the action execution was successful or not
successful.title: Successful

tools.name: Upload video
tools.description: Uploads a video from a local file path to a YouTube channel; the video file must be in a YouTube-supported format.

categoryId.description: YouTube category ID (e.g., '22' for People & Blogs). See YouTube Data API docs for a full list of category IDs.
categoryId.title: Category Id

description.description: Detailed description of the video content, optionally including keywords and context.
description.title: Description
examples: A detailed walkthrough of my latest project, showcasing all its features.

privacyStatus.description: Privacy status: 'public', 'private' (uploader/specified users only), or 'unlisted' (link accessible, not publicly listed).
privacyStatus.title: Privacy Status

tags.description: List of keyword tags (strings) for the video, used to improve discoverability.
tags.title: Tags

videoFilePath.title: FileUploadable
videoFilePath.description: Video file to upload. Provide a FileUploadable object with valid s3key, mimetype, and name.

response_data.description: Video resource returned by YouTube Data API videos.insert (upload). The response includes only the resource parts requested in the 'part' parameter. Some parts/fields are visible only to the channel's authorized owner.
response_data.title: Response Data

error.title: Error

successful.description: Whether or not the action execution was successful or not
successful.title: Successful

tools.name: Video details
tools.description: Retrieves specified information parts (e.g., snippet, contentDetails, statistics) for a YouTube video, identified by its ID.

id.description: The YouTube video ID (typically an 11-character string) for which details are to be retrieved.
id.title: Id

part.description: Comma-separated list of video resource parts that the API response will include. Valid parts: 'snippet' (title, description, thumbnails), 'contentDetails' (duration, definition, dimension), 'statistics' (view count, like count, comment count), 'status' (upload status, privacy status), 'player' (embed HTML), 'topicDetails' (associated topics), 'recordingDetails' (recording location and date), 'liveStreamingDetails' (live broadcast details), and 'localizations' (localized metadata).
part.title: Part

response_data.title: Response Data
